metadata.othernotes:
Background:

-In Fire Emblem Fates, you can get additional characters by romantically pairing two of your existing units. Upon reaching support level ''S'', an extra chapter is unlocked, which allows you to recruit the descendant of those characters.

Mitama is one such character, being the daughter of Azama and whoever he gets paired up with. In this case, her mother is Corrin, a decision inspired by the fact that I did so in my playthrough. As with the other child units, she was sent away to an alternate realm (a ''Deeprealm'') to protect her from the war which the main realm is facing.

In adition to being (relatively) secluded, the flow of time is faster within the Deeprealms, so these children become adults within a very short period of time on the main realm. In some cases, they become older than their parents.

As a side consequence of this diverging time flow, the parents tend to rarely visit their children, leaving their rearing to caretakers who live in that paricular Deeprealm. In Mitama's case, she was brought up in a shrine by the shrine priestesses, who had a plethora of poetry books, mainly about tanka and haiku.

From this, a young Mitama started writing haiku to express her loneliness and her desire to see her parents more. As she grew up, her interest bloomed into a deep fondness for writing haiku in particular.

Eventually, the Deeprealm in which she lives gets invaded. After a battle ensues, she joins her parents' army.

If all this sounds typically japanese, that's because the country that her father is from (Hoshido) is basically medieval Japan with a different name.

Personality:

Personality-wise, Mitama is very lazy, dedicating almost all of her free time to sleeping and writing, and rarely going outside unless she has to. Along her supports, she becomes slightly more proactive.

She can also be a very fatalistic and cynical person, believing that we are all slaves to fate, and expresses herself in a direct, although polite, manner.

Despite her laziness and pessimism, she has a caring side as well: she cares about her family, desiring affection from her father, and she takes seriously her duties as a healer whenever people get injured.

Sexuality-wise, I wrote Mitama as a forward person, who doesn't conceal her attraction towards other people. She is bisexual, although she has no experience with men, something that she would like to remedy by coming to this game. In terms of personality, she prefers people who are similar to her.
